179
00:12:00,940 --> 00:12:03,050
I'll describe that
pipeline in the next slide.

180
00:12:03,589 --> 00:12:07,050
The reason this constraint is
architecturally important is trust.

181
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:11,920
An enterprise cannot state its
tax compliance on AI-generated

182
00:12:12,030 --> 00:12:14,010
code that hasn't been validated.

183
00:12:14,370 --> 00:12:16,620
The pipeline is what earns that trust

184
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:21,440
The four validation layers are
herein, we are talking about

185
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:22,450
the four validation layer.

186
00:12:22,950 --> 00:12:28,080
This validation pipeline are structured
for the production rollout process.

187
00:12:29,020 --> 00:12:33,800
These four validation layers are
static code analysis, syntax, logic,

188
00:12:34,180 --> 00:12:37,020
and standards compliant- compliance.

189
00:12:37,980 --> 00:12:42,260
Regression testing, verifying that the
new rule doesn't break any existing rules.

190
00:12:42,580 --> 00:12:45,960
Differential testing, comparing outputs
between old and new rule versions to

191
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:48,820
identify unintended behavioral changes.

192
00:12:49,279 --> 00:12:53,759
And formal property checks, a mathematical
verification that the rule satisfies

193
00:12:53,809 --> 00:12:55,640
boundary condition and extremes.

194
00:12:56,140 --> 00:13:01,070
Only after all four layer pass
does the code move to production

195
00:13:01,089 --> 00:13:05,370
