196
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:08,240
We used a stage deployment model.

197
00:13:08,740 --> 00:13:12,380
Shadow deployment first, where
the new rules runs in parallel

198
00:13:12,490 --> 00:13:14,320
without affecting live transaction.

199
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:19,470
The canary testing, activating for
a small percentage of traffic, then

200
00:13:19,470 --> 00:13:23,339
gradual activation, expanding the
rollout with a continuous monitoring,

201
00:13:23,610 --> 00:13:28,280
and finally full deployment with rollback
capability remaining active throughout.

202
00:13:28,780 --> 00:13:32,950
The stage approach means that a
rule error will affect a fraction

203
00:13:32,950 --> 00:13:37,230
