235
00:15:16,180 --> 00:15:18,029
First, transaction-level traces.

236
00:15:18,239 --> 00:15:22,389
Every tax calculation is logged
with the exact rule version and the

237
00:15:22,389 --> 00:15:24,609
specific inputs that were applied.

238
00:15:25,009 --> 00:15:30,099
You can replay any transaction and
see precisely what logic was executed.

239
00:15:30,519 --> 00:15:34,599
Second, rule pro- rule
provenance tracking.

240
00:15:34,830 --> 00:15:39,879
Each rule in the system is linked
back to the specific regulatory text

241
00:15:40,350 --> 00:15:44,839
that generated it, the statute, the
guidance document, the effective date.

242
00:15:45,409 --> 00:15:49,909
There is no rule in the system that
cannot be traced to its legal source.

243
00:15:50,689 --> 00:15:52,259
Third, system-level observability.

244
00:15:52,919 --> 00:15:57,219
Drift detection, SLA monitoring, and
error tracking by jurisdiction, and

245
00:15:57,229 --> 00:16:01,049
automated rollback triggered when
an- when anomalies are detected.

246
00:16:01,589 --> 00:16:05,080
These three layers together mean
that when a tax auditor asks,

247
00:16:05,179 --> 00:16:06,589
"How did you calculate this?"

248
00:16:06,899 --> 00:16:09,859
The answer is always available,
always traceable, always defensible

249
00:16:10,359 --> 00:16:14,619
I want to share five hard-won lessons
from real enterprise dep-deployments

250
00:16:14,639 --> 00:16:18,709
of agentic compliance system, including
the work we have done at Amazon.

251
00:16:19,219 --> 00:16:22,529
Lesson one: confidence estimation
matters more than accuracy.

252
00:16:22,529 --> 00:16:27,649
The ability of the system to know
when it doesn't know and to escalate

253
00:16:27,699 --> 00:16:32,279
pro-appropriately is what separates
a prototype from a production system.

254
00:16:32,739 --> 00:16:37,249
Uncertainty quantification
drives self's safe escalation.

255
00:16:38,169 --> 00:16:42,039
Lesson two: DSL design is a
strategic intellectual property.

256
00:16:42,129 --> 00:16:45,519
The quality of a domain-specific
language determines the quality

257
00:16:45,519 --> 00:16:46,999
of everything downstream.

258
00:16:47,339 --> 00:16:50,259
Invest early in getting the DSL right.

259
00:16:50,759 --> 00:16:55,949
Lesson three: regulatory data inputs
vary significantly by jurisdiction.

260
00:16:55,949 --> 00:16:59,039
Some governments publish
machine-readable regulation.

261
00:16:59,279 --> 00:17:01,429
Other publish PDF scanned from paper.

262
00:17:01,879 --> 00:17:05,719
Your ingestion layer need to
handle both and needs to score

263
00:17:05,719 --> 00:17:08,009
its own confidence accordingly.

264
00:17:08,509 --> 00:17:13,029
Lesson four: identify-- identity
and access management integration

265
00:17:13,029 --> 00:17:14,399
is essential for audit.

266
00:17:14,799 --> 00:17:19,449
Every human approval action in
the governance dashboard must be

267
00:17:19,509 --> 00:17:22,189
tied to an authenticated identity.

268
00:17:22,849 --> 00:17:27,159
The audit log is only valuable
if it is tamper evident.

269
00:17:27,659 --> 00:17:28,673
And lesson five, the most important
governance maturity determines deployment

270
00:17:28,673 --> 00:17:28,726
success more than model accuracy.

271
00:17:28,726 --> 00:17:29,509
You can have a state-of-the-art LLM.

272
00:17:30,009 --> 00:17:34,299
If your organization hasn't defined
who approves rule changes, what the

273
00:17:34,309 --> 00:17:37,919
escalation thresholds are, and how
rollbacks are authorized, system will

274
00:17:37,939 --> 00:17:40,429
stall at the first high-stake decision.

275
00:17:41,109 --> 00:17:45,839
My practical recommendation is
start with simple generation, single

276
